-- Germans Increase Flat-Screen TV Purchases Before World Cup, Focus Reports
-- Holger Elfes
-- 2010-06-26T11:20:25Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-06-26/germans-increase-flat-screen-tv-purchases-before-world-cup-focus-reports.html

          
          
             Germans are buying more flat-screen
televisions to watch the soccer World Cup,  Focus  reported,
citing a survey by consumer research institute GfK SE.  
 Germans bought 400,000 more televisions between January and
June compared with the 1.8 million units that were sold in the
same period of 2009, the newsmagazine said in the e-mailed
preview of a report to be published June 28.  
 Samsung Electronics Co Ltd. increased its market share by 5
percentage points to 28 percent in the period, while Koninklijke
Philips Electronics NVâ€™s market share declined six percentage
points to 12 percent, according to Focus.  
